13-14 March - Spaghetti Bordelaise 

Garlic and Oil

- 8  tablespoon (1 stick) butter
- 6  tablespoon olive oil
- 3  tablespoon chopped fresh garlic
- 1  teaspoon salt
- 2  tablespoon fresh minced parsley 
- 12 oz spaghetti
- grated Parmesan cheese
- black pepper

Melt butter over low heat add olive oil, then garlic and salt. Cook 5-6 minutes until garlic begins to brown. Remove from heat and remove garlic from sauce. Stir in parsley. Cook spaghetti. Drain spaghetti and return to pot, pour on sauce and stir over low heat for 1 minute. Remove from heat, cover pot and let stand for 5 minutes. Mix again and add cheese 
